title.narrative: China: Qinghai Xining Urban Transport Project

description.narrative: The proposed Project Development Objective (PDO) is to enable Xining residents to travel between the city center and the western part of the city in a fast, efficient, and safe manner, through strategic improvements to Wusixi Road, a major transport and urban development corridor.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Financial management | Description :Qinghai Province shall furnish the audited financial statements to the Banknot later than six months after the end of each fiscal year. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Implementation arrangements | Description :Qinghai Province shall maintain throughout the period ofimplementation of the Project an organizational structure with composition, powers, functions, funds, staffing, facilities andother resources satisfactory to the Bank. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Implementation plan | Description :Qinghai Province shall cause Xining Municipality to prepare and furnish tothe Bank by November 30 in each year, starting from 2014, an annual implementation plan, summarizing the implementation progress ofthe Project for the said year and the Project activitiesto be undertaken for the following calendar year. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Reporting | Description :Qinghai Province shall, and shall cause Xining Municipality to monitor and evaluate theprogress of the Project and prepare semi-annual Project Reports, including project indicators by March 15 and September 15 in eachyear, starting from September 15, 2014. | Frequency :SemiAnnual

Finance Agreement :Safeguards | Description :Qinghai Province shall implement, or shall cause the Xining Municipality or itsagencies to implement the EMP, the RAP and the RPF in a manner and substance satisfactory to the Bank. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS
